Sunil Potti is Group Vice President and General Managerr of the Cloud Platforms Networking group at Citrix. Prior to this role, Potti worked with the Citrix NetScaler® team in his role as Vice President of Product Management and Product Marketing.
Potti joined Citrix from F5 Networks, where he was the Vice President of the Acceleration and Virtualization Group. Prior to F5, he co-founded and led all product efforts for Application-Oriented Networking at Cisco. Potti’s background includes co-founding and heading products at Synchrony, an eCRM startup that was acquired by Divine. Before that, he worked at Sybase in various roles, including leading the Sybase Central Architecture team. Potti has a Master’s degree in computer science and engineering from Pennsylvania State University.



